Key Features
* G10 
* Ambi Notch Standard
* Thumb Notch Standard
* CNC Machined
* Machined to fit any 1911 frame
* Fully De-horned
* This listing is for a set of gun grips ONLY

As cut the design provides an aggressive, slip free, no-nonsense grip for you 1911. However the grips and can be sanded to a smoother texture depending on customer preference. The grips are very competitively priced with lot of colors to choose from, options for every full size 1911 and choice of thickness.

The material is called G10 and its one of the best materials for handgun grips and the only one that can provide this look. Its much tougher than wood or acrylic... it won't absorb moisture and doesn't scratch very easy. The material is tough as nails and will last normal shooters a life time.

The grips will fit nearly all guns...and look about the same as the photos regardless of options, G10 can vary a little bit in color and thickness of grips can affect the look slightly. But I try to make the most attractive grip possible regardless of any variation. There are only a couple guns the grips won't fit and they are the Llama 1911, Girsan 1911 (metric bolt heads) and double stack 1911's.

I can custom make these to fit ANY bottom cut

**Bottom Cuts:
Standard Bevel - Most people need this option.... Has a 30 degree taper and a notch for the MSP

Magwell - If your gun has a magwell you probably want this option, straight 90 cut on the bottom with a covered MSP 

Wilson 188 Magwell - If you want to install a Wilson Combat 188 magwell you need this option (PT1911 requires slight modifications... basically filing the hooks about.020")

Other Bottom Cuts (Full Size ONLY... Leave a Note on Checkout or Send Email)

Bobtail - you probably have an Ed Brown or Dan Wesson, bottom corner of the grip is cut off and beveled

Round Butt - The bottom corner of the grip is rounded, Sig Nightmare, S&W E-Series, Kimber Super Carry Pro

title: For Sale:  Kel-Tec RFB 308 bullpup Green Hunter 24" Barrel
postcontent: RFB stands for Rifle, Forward-ejecting Bullpup. Why forward-ejecting? Because it allows the RFB to be the first truly ambidextrous 7.62 NATO Bullpup ever developed. The patented, dual-extractor system maintains control of the case from the moment it leaves the magazine and upon firing, pulls the fired case from the chamber and lifts them to push them into an ejection chute above the barrel, where they exit. The Bullpup configuration and tilting-block mechanism allow the 18" model to be only 26.1" long, or as much as 14" shorter in overall length than its competitors with equal barrel lengths. Furthermore, the stock and mechanism cross-section is similar to a conventional rifle, in stark contrast to existing Bullpup rifles. The RFB is also the safest Bullpup ever developed because the breech is separated from the shooters face by two layers of 1.6 mm steel. In the highly unlikely event of a case rupture, gas expansion is directed downwards through the magazine well to protect the shooters head and face.The RFB is a short-stroke gas piston operated semi-automatic rifle in 7.62 mm NATO caliber. It accepts standard metric FAL type magazines which work "drop free" and do not need to be tilted in. One 20 round magazine is included*. Barrels on current models are 18" long, with a chrome lined bore and chamber. The muzzle is threaded 5/8x24 TPI and comes equipped with our A2-style Flash Hider*. Longer barrel lengths of 24" available as the hunter variant. All controls are fully ambidextrous; the reciprocating operating handle can be switched to either side. The trigger mechanism is second to no other Bullpup ever built and better than nearly all commercial semi-auto rifles. The safety disconnects the trigger and blocks the hammer action. A Mil-Spec Picatinny rail is attached rigidly to the barrel. No open sights are provided, allowing the user to select from the very best new optics and sight systems available. The RFB comes with a two point sling that can be easily configured to suit the user's preference. Available accessories include a free-floating, four-sided Picatinny forend, bipod mounts, a removable bayonet lug for use with NATO style bayonets including our own Folding Bayonet, and many more.Last one! $1599!!

title: For Sale:  Gun Cleaning Services
postcontent:
Hello all, 

I am a novice gunsmith who is working towards an official certification. To help get there, I am offering gun cleaning services for a reduced fee. 

Have a collection? Or that nice hunting rifle that saw some use (hopefully getting your nice haul this year) but hasn't had the opportunity to be cleaned up? 

Save yourself the time and hassle, I can do pickups, drop-offs, multiple item collections, etc. I have experience with most weapons systems, anything I am not 100% comfortable with will be turned away without any cost to the customer. 

Prices will depend on the extensiveness of cleaning. If you are looking for a quick internals maintenance/lube, and a clean bore, that could be a pretty low cost. However, if you're looking for a pickup of multiple ARs with 1000+ rounds through it, and a few hours of scraping to be done, that will cost more.

My initial point, in doing this however, is to afford the closing costs on certificates and final classes required, and to build a portfolio. Anyone who is willing to put in a word, and leave a reference, I am sure we can work out some other deal in these regards.

Thanks for any consideration, I look forward to any inquiries you may have, feel free to send them over.

Have a Merry Christmas, all!
